main event: A bright white object was observed moving west at an estimated speed of 85-100 mph over Toledo, Ohio on August 12, 1965.
interesting points: The object showed a sudden change in direction, then continued on a different course.
The object was described as a 'dirty looking smudgy white object' with no distinct shape or outline.
The witness observed the object for approximately 15 minutes.
The witness used binoculars and eyeglasses to observe the object.
The witness estimated the distance to the object to be 0.5 to 1 mile away.
